      "note": "Paper reports only a single monoexponential response half-time τ1/2 = 1.75 ± 0.11 ms for the depolarizing step (room temperature, 1058 Hz frame rate); converted to a time constant via τ = t½/ln2 = 1.75/0.693 = 2.53 ms. Separate activation/deactivation time constants were not resolved, so on and off use the same symmetric value.",
